Description: Iron finger-ring; oval bezel with engraved design: winged female figure (Fortuna-Isis?) wearing horns and disk; she is draped and carries a sistrum and rudder.
Bibliographic references: Finger Ring / Catalogue of the Finger Rings, Greek, Etruscan, and Roman, in the Departments of Antiquities, British Museum (1463)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Augustus Wollaston Franks
